    <summary>uattool simplifies running Unreal Engine's Unreal Automation Tool</summary>
    <description>
    uattool is a helper executable that finds the versions of Unreal Engine that you have installed on your system. It then allows you to run a UAT command against them, reducing the number of times you've got to copy-and-paste the path of the `RunUAT.bat` script.

    To see the versions of Unreal Engine you have installed, run:
    ```
    uattool --list
    ```

    To run a command, specify the version* and the uat command. For example, to build a plugin for Unreal Engine 5.2-5.4, simply run::
    ```
    uattool 5.2+5.3+5.4 BuildPlugin -Plugin="C:/path/to/plugin.uplugin" -Package="C:/PluginPack"
    ```
    </description>
